nnotierten Gebrauchsformen des Psalmenbuchs in Verbindung gebracht.  aThe miniatures in the Stuttgart Psalter reflect the text in its totally direct sense, and thus give the Carolingian manuscript a special status, along with the Utrecht Psalter. Felix Heinzer undertakes a detailed examination of the functional connection behind this form of illustration. In the process, he also incorporates the Carolingian striving for valid texts together with contexts of apotropaic usage.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aIllumination of books and manuscripts, GermanzGermanyzStuttgart. 0aIllumination of books and manuscripts, MedievalzGermanyzStuttgart. 0aPsalterszGermanyzStuttgart. 4aMiniatur. 4aStuttgarter Psalter. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aSchmidt, Paul Gerhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2005z9783110277111oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2005z9783110276886oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311018051040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311090369040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110903690423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110903690/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2005  aZDB-23-DGGb2005  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014